
[1]meritorious

   MERITO'RIOUS, a. Deserving of reward or of notice, regard, fame or
   happiness, or of that which shall be a suitable return for services or
   excellence of any kind. We applaud the meritorious services of the
   laborer, the soldier and the seaman. We admire the meritorious labors
   of a Watts, a Doddridge, a Carey and a Martyn. We rely for salvation on
   the meritorious obedience and sufferings of Christ.
